Class StockStatisticsResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.cam.cl.juliet.common.Container
      • uk.ac.cam.cl.juliet.common.QueryResponse
        • uk.ac.cam.cl.juliet.common.StockStatisticsResponse
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class StockStatisticsResponse
extends QueryResponse
    This is the response message to a StockStatisticsRequest, returning the price of the last trade, the total trade volume, the highest and the lowest trade price, change between the two last trade prices and the spread of the order book.
    Author:
    Lucas Sonnabend
    See Also:
    StockStatisticsRequest, Serialized Form

      • StockStatisticsResponse

        public StockStatisticsResponse(long id,
                       boolean result,
                       float pLastTradePrice,
                       long pTotalTradeVolume,
                       float pHighestTradePrice,
                       float pLowestTradePrice,
                       float pChange,
                       float pSpread)
        Create a new StockStatisticsResponse
        Parameters:
        id - The packet ID of the corresponding request packet
        result - A boolean indicator whether the query was processed successfully
        pLastTradePrice - The price of the last trade
        pTotalTradeVolume - The accumulated volume of all trades
        pHighestTradePrice - The highest trade price seen so far
        pLowestTradePrice - The lowest trade price seen so far
        pChange - The absolute change between the last trade price and the second last trade price
        pSpread - The difference between the highest bid and the lowest offer in the orderbook
